<TABLE WIDTH="100%" BORDER="0" CELLSPACING="0" CELLPADDING="7">
    <TR>
	<TD>
            <P>
            <FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Lucida Grande,Geneva,Arial">
            If the maximum mouse speed at the options dialog doesn't fit your needs, you should go to the Quake console and experiment with the variable &quot;sensitivity&quot;. Entering &quot;sensitivity&quot; without any parameter will report the current mouse sensitivity value. Entering &quot;sensitivity x&quot;, for example &quot;sensitivity 44&quot;, will set the mouse speed to the value of x.
            </FONT>
            </P>
